sfpsSysConfigTable.name: sfpsSysConfigTable
sfpsSysConfigTable.description: This table contains the configuration and aministrative information of each SFPS instance. Essentially, a separate SFPS instance exists for each switch module. If SFPS is not configured on a module, than an entry will not exist.

sfpsSysConfigEntry.name: sfpsSysConfigEntry
sfpsSysConfigEntry.description: Each entry specifies the SFPS configuration for the SFPS instance.

sfpsSysConfigSwitchInstance.name: sfpsSysConfigSwitchInstance
sfpsSysConfigSwitchInstance.description: Switch Identifier to designate the instance of this entry.

sfpsSysConfigAdminStatus.name: sfpsSysConfigAdminStatus
sfpsSysConfigAdminStatus.description: The administrative status of the switch.

sfpsSysConfigAdminReset.name: sfpsSysConfigAdminReset
sfpsSysConfigAdminReset.description: Setting reset will cause a soft reset of the switch.

sfpsSysConfigOperStatus.name: sfpsSysConfigOperStatus
sfpsSysConfigOperStatus.description: Displays the operational status of the switch.

sfpsSysConfigOperTime.name: sfpsSysConfigOperTime
sfpsSysConfigOperTime.description: Displays the operation uptime of the switch.

sfpsSysConfigLastChange.name: sfpsSysConfigLastChange
sfpsSysConfigLastChange.description: Displays the number of time ticks since the last operational status change.

sfpsSysConfigVersion.name: sfpsSysConfigVersion
sfpsSysConfigVersion.description: Displays the version of this image.

sfpsSysConfigMIBRev.name: sfpsSysConfigMIBRev
sfpsSysConfigMIBRev.description: Displays the MIB version of the Engine component.

sfpsSysConfigHostCtrlPort.name: sfpsSysConfigHostCtrlPort
sfpsSysConfigHostCtrlPort.description: Displays the logical port number for the Host Control Port. The Host Control Port is the port that unknown packets are sent to for call processing.

sfpsSysConfigSwitchMode.name: sfpsSysConfigSwitchMode
sfpsSysConfigSwitchMode.description: Displays the mode that the switch is running.

sfpsSysConfigSwitchMAC.name: sfpsSysConfigSwitchMAC
sfpsSysConfigSwitchMAC.description: Displays the Switch's Base MAC address.

sfpsSysConfigMgmtAccessType.name: sfpsSysConfigMgmtAccessType
sfpsSysConfigMgmtAccessType.description: Determines whether the port can be used for management only or to be also used as an Access port.

sfpsSysStatsTable.name: sfpsSysStatsTable
sfpsSysStatsTable.description: This table contains the statistics information fo each SFPS switch instance. Essentially, a separate SFPS instance exists for each switch module. If SFPS is not configured on a module, than an entry will not exist.

sfpsSysStatsEntry.name: sfpsSysStatsEntry
sfpsSysStatsEntry.description: Each entry contains the SFPS statistics for the SFPS instance.

sfpsSysStatsSwitchInstance.name: sfpsSysStatsSwitchInstance
sfpsSysStatsSwitchInstance.description: The primary index to the SFPS switch table. This identifies the SFPS switch for which the entry exists.

sfpsSysStatsAdminStatus.name: sfpsSysStatsAdminStatus
sfpsSysStatsAdminStatus.description: Sets the administrative state of the SFPS switch statistics. Writing a value of enabled(3) causes these counters to become active for this SFPS switch instance. Writing a value of disabled(2) causes these counters to become inactive for this SFPS switch instance.

sfpsSysStatsReset.name: sfpsSysStatsReset
sfpsSysStatsReset.description: Resets the SFPS switch counters for this SFPS switch instance. Writing a value of reset(2) resets the SFPS switch counters to 0 and causes sfpsSysStatsOperTime to also be reset to 0.

sfpsSysStatsOperTime.name: sfpsSysStatsOperTime
sfpsSysStatsOperTime.description: Indicates the amount of time (# of time ticks) that the SFPS switch statistics have been active for this SFPS swtich instance.

sfpsSysStatsInPkts.name: sfpsSysStatsInPkts
sfpsSysStatsInPkts.description: Indicates the total number of SFPS packets that have been received, on this SFPS switch instance, during the time of sfpsSysStatsOperTime.

sfpsSysStatsOutPkts.name: sfpsSysStatsOutPkts
sfpsSysStatsOutPkts.description: Indicates the total number of SFPS packets that have been switched, on this SFPS switch instance, during the time of sfpsSysStatsOperTime.

sfpsSysStatsDiscardPkts.name: sfpsSysStatsDiscardPkts
sfpsSysStatsDiscardPkts.description: Indicates the total number of SFPS packets that have been discarded, on this SFPS switch instance, during the time of sfpsSysStatsOperTime.

sfpsSysStatsFilteredPkts.name: sfpsSysStatsFilteredPkts
sfpsSysStatsFilteredPkts.description: Indicates the total number of SFPS packets that have been filtered, on this SFPS switch instance, during the time of sfpsSysStatsOperTime.

sfpsSysStatsInOctets.name: sfpsSysStatsInOctets
sfpsSysStatsInOctets.description: Indicates the total number of SFPS octets that have been received, on this SFPS switch instance, during the time of sfpsSysStatsOperTime.

sfpsSysStatsOutOctets.name: sfpsSysStatsOutOctets
sfpsSysStatsOutOctets.description: Indicates the total number of SFPS octets that have been switched, on this SFPS switch instance, during the time of sfpsSysStatsOperTime.

sfpsSysStatsDiscardOctets.name: sfpsSysStatsDiscardOctets
sfpsSysStatsDiscardOctets.description: Indicates the total number of SFPS octets that have been discarded, on this SFPS switch instance, during the time of sfpsSysStatsOperTime.

sfpsSysStatsFilteredOctets.name: sfpsSysStatsFilteredOctets
sfpsSysStatsFilteredOctets.description: Indicates the total number of SFPS octets that have been filtered, on this SFPS switch instance, during the time of sfpsSysStatsOperTime.

sfpsATMSvcHistoryEventVccHand.name: sfpsATMSvcHistoryEventVccHand

sfpsATMSvcHistoryEventVpi.name: sfpsATMSvcHistoryEventVpi
sfpsATMSvcHistoryEventVpi.description: vpi associated with connection on Port Number

sfpsATMSvcHistoryEventVci.name: sfpsATMSvcHistoryEventVci
sfpsATMSvcHistoryEventVci.description: vci associated with connection on Port Number

sfpsATMSvcHistoryMgrVerb.name: sfpsATMSvcHistoryMgrVerb
sfpsATMSvcHistoryMgrVerb.description: allows you to reset the SvcHistoryEvent table disable logging so no new entries are compiled in the SvcHistoryEvent table enable logging so new entries are added to the SvcHistoryEvent table enable logging in the SvcHistoryEvent table so that when the max number of entries is reached the table is full and doesn't wrap around and continue adding entries

sfpsATMSvcHistoryMgrSvcHistoryWraps.name: sfpsATMSvcHistoryMgrSvcHistoryWraps
sfpsATMSvcHistoryMgrSvcHistoryWraps.description: displays if the table is going to wrap

sfpsATMSvcHistoryMgrLogState.name: sfpsATMSvcHistoryMgrLogState
sfpsATMSvcHistoryMgrLogState.description: displays whether the table is enabled to log new entries or not and if it is enabled whether the table will wrap

sfpsATMSvcHistoryMgrEntriesCount.name: sfpsATMSvcHistoryMgrEntriesCount
sfpsATMSvcHistoryMgrEntriesCount.description: displays the number of current entries from the beginnning of the table (not from before it wrapped)
